### <%= @class_header %> : register_status_callback()
``` lua
local <%= @variable_text %>	-- example <%= @variable_text %>
local function callback()
  print( "I got hit by a Breaking attack." )
end

<%= @variable_text %>:register_status_callback( Hit.Breaking, callback )
```

Registers a **`function`** that will be executed when the <%= @class_name %> is hit by an attack that has some specific <%= @link_hit %> flags.

#### Function Call
`<%= @variable_text %>:register_status_callback( hit_flags, callback )`

#### Parameters
<%= @link_hit %> `hit_flags`<br>
	&emsp;_A move with these <%= @link_hit %> flags will trigger the callback._<br>
**`function`** `callback`<br>
	&emsp;_This is the **`function`** that will be called when an <%= @link_entity %> is hit by an attack with one of those flags._<br>
